sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
[[File:Screen_Shot_2013-06-16_at_12.18.27_AM.png|thumb|left|Jon Snow finds Ghost as a pup]]

After five direwolf puppies are found by [[Robb Stark|Robb S]][[Robb Stark|tark]] and taken, one for each one of the [[House Stark|Stark]] children, Jon Snow finds an albino direwolf pup, the runt of the litter. [[Theon Greyjoy]] cruelly acknowledges that the wolf is like Snow.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Jon Snow takes Ghost with him when he joins the [[Night's Watch]] and uses him to threaten [[Rast]] in the middle of the night, warning him that â&euro;&oelig;no one touches [[Samwell Tarly|Sam]]â&euro;?. Ghost stands over Rast, snarling.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

While Jon and Sam say their oath of fealty to the Night's Watch in front of aÂ [[heart tree]] north of the [[Wall]], just inside the eaves of theÂ [[Haunted Forest]], GhostÂ finds the corpses of two rangers assigned to [[Benjen Stark]],[[Othor]] and Ser [[Jafer Flowers]], and brings one of their severed handsÂ back to Jon and a horrified Sam.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[You Win or You Die]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:Ghost.png|thumb|Ghost snarls at Rast.]]

When Jon is confined to quarters for threatening Ser [[Alliser Thorne]], Ghost begins to whine at the door in the middle of the night. Jon understands something is wrong and follows the wolf to the Lord Commander's quarters. Suddenly the door shuts and Ghost is locked outside the room. Jon encounters the undead Othor, risen as a [[wight]], and saves the life of the [[Jeor Mormont|Lord Commander]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

When Jon tries to leave and join Robb in his [[War of the Five Kings|war]] against the [[House Lannister|Lannisters]], Ghost leaves with him, but also returns back once Jon returns to the Wall.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Fire and Blood]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
[[File:GhostDirewolfSeason2.png|thumb|left|Ghost accompanies Jon north.]]Ghost follows his master Jon Snow and the rest of the Night's Watch as they venture deep into [[Beyond the Wall|wildling territory]]Â in their [[Great Ranging]]. While the Night's Watch men stay at [[Craster's Keep]]Â to rest and inform themselves about Mance Rayder,Â one of Craser'sÂ daughters, [[Gilly]],Â is scared by Ghost when the white direwolf approaches her, attracted by a dead rabbit she's holding. Samwell Tarly, who had already took notice of her, tells Ghost to get away.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Night Lands]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Along with the black brothers, Ghost climbs the Fist of the First Men.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Ghost of Harrenhal]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â Later, when Jon asks to join Qhorin's raiders, Ghost follows, but as they travel, the direwolf separates from the group and ultimately disappears, despite Jon's calls for Ghost to stay with them.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Old Gods and the New]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
[[File:Ghost_Attacks_a_Wite.jpg|thumb|202px|Ghost saves Sam's life.]]
Following the [[Battle of the Fist of the First Men|attack]] of the [[White Walkers]] against the Night's Watch at the [[Fist of the First Men]], Ghost saves Sam from a [[Wight]], giving Lord Commander Jeor MormontÂ the chance to destroy the wight with fire.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Dohaeris]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Then, Ghost accompanies the Night's Watch survivors to Craster's Keep but refuses to enter this time. Instead he ventures back into the [[Haunted Forest]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Later, when Sam stumbles across [[Bran Stark]], [[Jojen Reed]], [[Meera Reed]], and [[Hodor]], he recognizes Bran due to the presence of [[Summer]], having spent enough time with Ghost to be able to recognize a direwolf.&lt;ref&gt;[[Mhysa]]&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
[[File:S04E5_-_Jon_Snow_&amp;_Ghost.png|thumb|left|Ghost reunites with his master Jon after being freed by Bran.]] Ghost has been captured and caged by the [[Betrayers|Mutineers]]. One night [[Karl Tanner]] orders [[Rast]] to feed Ghost, which he refers to as &quot;the beast&quot;. Rast taunts Ghost by pouring water in front of the cage. When Bran wargs into [[Summer]] he sees Ghost and runs towards him but falls into a trap.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; After [[Raid on Craster's Keep|escaping]] [[Craster's Keep]], [[Bran Stark]] and his companions release Ghost and Summer. Ghost remains nearby and kills Rast when he flees the massacre of his fellow mutineers. Afterward, Ghost reunites with Jon Snow after being apart for more than a year.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[First of His Name]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:Ghost_kills_Thenn.png|thumb|Ghost kills a Thenn warrior.]]

They arrive together at Castle Black, yet Alliser ThorneÂ orders Jon to lock him away.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Mockingbird]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â During the [[Battle of Castle Black]], Jon has SamwellÂ release Ghost so that he can help kill the wildlings raiding the castle. Immediately, Ghost lunges at a Thenn warrior and tears out his throat. He ultimately survives the battle.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Watchers on the Wall]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

